Interface ISerializableFileHandler

All Known Implementing Classes:
SerializableFileHandler
public interface ISerializableFileHandler
Defines the contract for serializing and deserializing objects to and from files using Java's standard serialization mechanism.
Since:
version 3.0
Version:
3.0
Author:
Juan Pablo Piedrahita Triana.

  • Method Details

    • serialize

      void serialize(String filename, Object element)
      Serializes the specified object and writes it to a file with the given filename.
      Parameters:
      filename - The path of the file where the object will be saved.
      element - The object to serialize. It should implement Serializable.

    • deserialize

      Object deserialize(String filename)
      Deserializes an object from the specified file and returns it.
      Parameters:
      filename - The path of the file to read the object from.
      Returns:
      The deserialized object, or null if an error occurs during deserialization.
